Everyone who has to eat fish in barebones living situations tends to prefer its organs. P. Linkola said the savory fish guts were his favorite part. Les Stroud says he loves freshly caught fish's liver and heart. One Bulgarian fisherman I know said he loves eating raw fish whole.

When you need the nutrients you tend to start to notice how appetizing the nutrient rich organs are. I remember also WW2 soldiers who were starving craved cod liver oil due to the fat-soluble vitamins there and spread it on slices of old dry bread like butter. Fish is a rich food
